# Tutor Stack Conventions

These rules apply only to GMAT Tutor (chat assistant) code inside `trainer/`.

## Auth

- Use `getSessionUserId()` from `@/lib/auth-session`. It returns `string | null`.
- Cookie name: `gmat_session`. JWT payload: `{ sub: userId }`. Do not introduce
  a second cookie or assume an `email` field on the session.
- Gate every tutor API route:

```ts
const userId = await getSessionUserId();
if (!userId) return new Response('Unauthorized', { status: 401 });
```

## Prisma

- Single client: `import { prisma } from '@/lib/prisma'`. Never instantiate a new
  `PrismaClient` in route handlers.
- Tutor models are prefixed `Tutor*`: `TutorConversation`, `TutorMessage`,
  `TutorChapterChunk`. Enums are `TutorMessageRole`, `TutorTier`.
- Schema changes go to `trainer/prisma/schema.prisma` and are applied via
  `npx prisma db push`.

## Streaming (Vercel AI SDK v4)

- Server: `streamText({ model: google(TUTOR_MODEL), system, messages, ... })`,
  return `result.toDataStreamResponse()`. Persist the assistant message in
  `onFinish`. Never invent a custom SSE format.
- Client: `useChat` from `'ai/react'` with the route at `/api/tutor/chat`.

## Theming

The trainer uses CSS custom properties: `var(--bg)`, `var(--panel)`,
`var(--border)`, `var(--ink)`, `var(--muted)`, `var(--accent)`,
`var(--accent-mute)`. New tutor UI must use these — not hard-coded colors and
not new Tailwind palettes.

## File layout

```
trainer/
  src/
    app/
      tutor/page.tsx              # split-pane workspace
      api/tutor/chat/route.ts
      api/tutor/conversations/[...]
    components/tutor/             # PascalCase components
    lib/
      gemini.ts                   # provider + TUTOR_MODEL
      tutor/
        system-prompt.ts
        retrieve.ts
  scripts/index-chapters.mjs      # parses chapters into TutorChapterChunk
```

## Streaming + persistence pattern

Within `POST /api/tutor/chat`:

1. `getSessionUserId()` gate.
2. Parse `{ messages, conversationId?, chapterSlug?, anchor?, tier }`.
3. `retrieve({ query, chapterSlug, k: 4 })` to get textbook chunks.
4. `ensureConversation` (create or load).
5. Persist the latest user message synchronously.
6. `streamText` with the system prompt; persist the assistant text in
   `onFinish`.
7. Return `toDataStreamResponse()` with `X-Conversation-Id` header.
